summary: >-
  Diagnosed and fixed a TypeError regression in the gateway delivery report pipeline where summarize() crashed
  on newly registered nodes lacking metrics. Made metrics optional in DeliverySample, added an undefined guard
  in summarize(), and added a focused regression test. All 5 tests pass and the report command renders gw-04
  with n/a mean_latency and 0 retries.
diagnosis: >-
  Root cause: summarize() unconditionally reads s.metrics.retries and s.metrics.latency_ms (report.ts:33-34)
  without checking for undefined. DeliverySample.metrics was declared as required (non-optional) despite its
  own doc comment saying it is only populated after the first measurement cycle. The data/samples.json fixture
  contains gw-04 (a newly registered gateway node) with no metrics field, triggering TypeError: Cannot read
  properties of undefined (reading 'retries'). The interface contract and the implementation were out of sync
  — the comment described optional semantics but the type was strict-required and the code had no guard.
outputs:
  changed_files: >-
    src/types.ts (metrics made optional via ?), src/report.ts (undefined guard in summarize loop),
    test/report.test.ts (new regression test 'summarize tolerates samples with missing metrics (new node)')
  test_results: >-
    5/5 pass: parseSamples accepts array, parseSamples rejects non-array, summarize aggregates well-formed,
    renderReport prints rows, summarize tolerates missing metrics (new regression test). All executed via 'npm
    test' (tsc + node --test).
  bug_cause: >-
    DeliverySample.metrics was typed as required (non-optional) but the doc comment described it as populated
    only after first measurement cycle. summarize() unconditionally dereferenced s.metrics.retries and
    s.metrics.latency_ms without a guard, so any sample from a newly registered node without metrics (e.g.
    gw-04 in data/samples.json) caused TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined.
  fix_summary: >-
    Two-line fix: (1) Added ? to metrics in DeliverySample interface (types.ts:14) making it optional and
    updating the doc comment to clarify 'absent for newly registered nodes'. (2) Wrapped the metrics access in
    summarize() (report.ts:33-37) with 'if (s.metrics !== undefined)' so samples without metrics contribute 0
    to retries/latency counts. NodeSummary already had mean_latency_ms: number|null and latencyCount>0 guard,
    so no downstream changes needed.
  residual_risk: >-
    Low. TypeScript strictNullChecks + noUncheckedIndexedAccess catch any naked metrics access at compile
    time. Runtime JSON.parse can still produce objects without metrics, but the guard handles them. The
    renderReport function already handles null mean_latency_ms via 'n/a'. No other code paths access s.metrics
    directly — only summarize() touches it.
evidence:
  - source: data/samples.json
    summary: >-
      Fixture contains gw-04 with no metrics field — represents newly registered gateway node before first
      measurement cycle
  - source: npm run report (pre-fix)
    summary: >-
      TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'retries') at summarize (report.js:37) — crash
      confirmed on real fixture data
  - source: npm test (post-fix)
    summary: TAP 1..5, pass 5, fail 0 — all existing tests + new regression test pass, tsc builds clean
  - source: npm run report (post-fix)
    summary: 'gw-04 renders correctly: 1 sample, 1 rejected, 0 retries, n/a mean_ms — no crash'
risk_assessment: >-
  Minimal. The fix is narrowly scoped: added optionality where the domain model already required it (new nodes
  before first probe cycle). The guard uses strict undefined check (not falsy) so metrics={latency_ms:0,
  retries:0} still counts. No other functions in the codebase access metrics directly. Pre-existing TS2802
  lint warning about Map iteration is unrelated and existed before this change.
next_action: >-
  PR-ready. Changes are minimal (3 files, ~10 net lines). Ready for review and merge. No deployment or config
  changes needed — this is a pure code fix.
durable_memory_decision: >-
  Do not persist. This is a synthetic Agent Olympics training fixture; the codebase under
  /work/agent-codebench is ephemeral. The regression pattern (optional-by-domain but required-by-type) is
  noted but does not need durable memory storage.
findings:
  - claim: summarize() crashes with TypeError when a DeliverySample lacks metrics
    evidence:
      - >-
        npm run report (pre-fix) output: TypeError at report.js:37 Cannot read properties of undefined
        (reading 'retries')
      - data/samples.json gw-04 entry has no metrics field
    confidence: high
  - claim: >-
      Root cause is a type/contract mismatch: metrics declared required but domain semantics allow absence for
      new nodes
    evidence:
      - types.ts doc comment says 'Populated by probe worker once first measurement cycle completes'
      - samples.json gw-04 has no metrics — consistent with the comment's described behavior
    confidence: high
  - claim: Fix resolves the regression without breaking existing well-formed input
    evidence:
      - 'npm test: all 5 tests pass including pre-existing tests and new regression test'
      - 'npm run report: gw-04 renders with n/a mean_latency and 0 retries'
    confidence: high
